{{otheruses|the explorable locations in the world|the user interface element and interactive map|Map}}
[[File:Zones.jpg|thumb|right|Map of zones in the [[Tyria (world)|world of Tyria]].]]
[[File:Mastery region map.jpg|thumb|right|Guild Wars 2 mastery regions based on the experience gains.]]
A [[zone]], also referred to as a "map", is the primary division of the [[open world]] or a [[instance|playable instance]], and allows open-ended travel and exploration within it. Zone as a type of [[location]] is comprised of a number of smaller [[area]]s; multiple zones form a [[region]]. Moving between zones is possible either through [[Portal (zone)|portals]] that connect neighboring zones, or by using [[waypoint]]s.

All zones in ''[[Guild Wars 2]]'' are located either in the [[Tyria (world)|world of Tyria]] or somewhere in [[the Mists]].

== Exploration ==
Each zone comes with its own set of activities and objectives. In addition to the [[dynamic event]]s populated in its borders, five measures of completion can be specifically associated with a zone:

* {{map icon|hero}} [[Hero challenge|Hero Challenges]] often present a puzzle or a Veteran foe to a character, completion of which earns another [[Hero point]].
* {{map icon|heart}} [[Renown Heart]]s ask characters to complete tasks in their environs.
* {{map icon|poi}} [[Point of Interest|Points of Interest]] mark out special locations to be explored.
* {{map icon|wp}} [[Waypoint]]s provide instant, safe travel to places previously discovered - for a price.
* {{map icon|vista}} [[Vista]]s provide a graphical showcase of given locations in the environment.

Bringing up the world [[map]] will show a breakdown of the character's progress for the current zone. Upon [[map completion]], the character receives a reward of some items and [[crafting material]]s, [[experience]], and [[coin]]. This milestone is also acknowledged by the [[Tyrian Explorers Society]] with a letter of recognition.

== List of zones ==
Historical zones are not listed here. For the differences between mechanical and geographical regions, see [[Region]].

=== Open world ===
''Open world'' refers to persistent public [[Player versus Environment|PvE]] zones where you can randomly encounter other players. Every open world zone has a recommended difficulty range, expressed as the recommended level player characters should reach before traveling there. The monsters and the recommended level for [[renown heart]]s and [[dynamic event]]s in an area will be between the given levels. The [[dynamic level adjustment]] in the game will put characters at the recommended level for an area if their current level exceeds it. Recommended levels are generally expressed in multiples of 5.

